The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 25: The countrys handicrafts exports grew about 2 per cent to $1.83 billion during 2009-10 because of growing demand in the US and Europe, Raj Malhotra, chairman of the Export Promotion Council for Handicrafts, said. During 2008-09, exports stood at $1.79 billion. Of the total items exported during 2009-10, the EU emerged as the major importer with a share of 40 per cent, followed by the US with 25 per cent.                            
	 New Delhi, April 25: The railways have suffered a loss of Rs 79 crore because of its indifferent attitude towards withdrawal of uneconomical stoppages, injudicious creation of passenger amenities and failure to augment coaches on time, the Comptroller and Auditor General said.                             
	 New Delhi, April 25: The Life Insurance Corporation has pumped over Rs 61,000 crore into the capital market during 2009-10. We have invested Rs 61,468 crore in the equity market for the year ended March which is almost 50 per cent higher than the previous fiscals, LIC executive director (investment operations) N. Mohanraj said.                             
	 New Delhi, April 25: Bharti Airtel has launched a SIM card, which enables global travellers to save up to 85 per cent on international calls. The SIM also allows outbound travellers to retain their local number.                             
	 Mumbai, April 25: Godrej Consumer Products Ltd plans to focus on the African market and has drawn-up a One Africa strategy to achieve this goal.                                                                                                                          
